Yankees-Tigers Playoff Opener Is Suspended by Rain in New York

-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 
2011-10-01T02:26:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-01/yankees-tigers-playoff-opener-is-suspended-by-rain-in-new-york.html
Game 1 of the American League
Division Series between the  New York Yankees  and  Detroit Tigers 
has been suspended by rain.   Play was halted tonight after the top of the second inning
with the score tied 1-1 at Yankee Stadium in New York. The game
was suspended after a delay of 1 hour, 17 minutes.  The game will resume tomorrow in New York at 8:37 p.m. with
the Yankees coming to bat in the bottom of the second inning.
Game 2 of the best-of-five Major League Baseball playoff series
has been pushed back to Oct. 2.   The Yankees had 22 games affected by weather during the
regular season, including a major league-high nine rainouts.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Erik Matuszewski at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net  